('d7a87ed1-a155-406a-acca-c5469779ab24', '519bfbbd-b6c2-4f04-9e24-328ab3d1d921', '1', 'Which of the following Neolithic sites is uniquely known for pit dwellings and the practice of burying domestic dogs with their masters?', 'निम्नलिखित में से कौन सा नवपाषाण स्थल विशेष रूप से गड्ढे वाले घरों (गर्तवास) और मालिकों के साथ पालतू कुत्तों को दफनाने की प्रथा के लिए जाना जाता है?', '["Mehrgarh","Chirand","Burzahom","Koldihwa"]', '["मेहरगढ़","चिरांद","बुर्जहोम","कोल्डीहवा"]', 2, 'Correct answer is C because Burzahom is famously known for pit dwellings and dog burials with their masters.
